subSubSection.paragraph:
COLORATION (
Figs. 1–4
). The carapace and tergites are yellowish brown, strongly black pigmented. The metasoma, telson, pedipalps and legs are yellowish brown. The metasoma ventral, mainly segment V black pigmented.

PEDIPALPS (
Figs. 9–14
). The pedipalps are sparsely hirsute and smooth. The femur bears four to five granulated carinae, the middle carina on internal surface could be incomplete indicated by several strong denticles. The patella bears eight carinae from which internal in both sexes and dorsal in females are granulated. The chela is without carinae. The movable fingers of pedipalps bear 13 cutting rows of denticles, every with external and internal denticles present, and five terminal denticles.

LEGS (
Figs. 185–188
). The tarsomeres bear two rows of short and strong spiniform setae on the ventral surface and numerous macrosetae on the other surfaces. Pedal spur of legs with solitary setae only. Femur bears only several macrosetae. Femur and patella with carinae well developed. Tibial spurs present and long on third and fourth legs and absent in the other legs.
